43 E Ohio St (at N Wabash Ave)
131 W Jefferson Ave (btwn Main St & Webster St)

tip.text: Ambience is great! Food, taste and portion is just right to accompany drinks. Nasi goreng is my favorite. Vast selection of cocktails is a plus although not all is good, tried 'Detergent' but weird!!

location.address: Jalan Radio Dalam Raya No. F11-11A, Radio Dalam
formattedAddress: Jalan Radio Dalam Raya No. F11-11A, Radio Dalam

tip.text: Laksa & asam pedas are must have! Can't order these two before 12pm (lunch time). Bfast menu valid before 12pm and quite limited. For strong coffee, opt for Kelantan. For milder one, Perak is good.
Roasted Duck is a must! Would love to try roasted pork and egg tarts on next visit as both sold out. Booking is very much advisable as traffic is high even on weekdays.

formattedAddress: #05-08/09 Ngee Ann City, Podium Block (391 Orchard Road)

venue.name: East Ocean Teochew Restaurant 東海潮洲酒家

tip.text: Best Belgian beers list! Chicken wings is a must! Ask for garlic dipping sauce, something not on the menu. Fish and chips is also great, batter seasoned nicely. Definitely regular visit when in town.
Two thumbs up on the wide range variety of sandwiches! Tried the new river lobster roll and it's amazing! Returned and had the scallop aglio olio which was also very nice, light balanced taste.

formattedAddress: Central Department Store, Ground Floor, East Mall - Grand Indonesia (Jl. MH. Thamrin No. 1)
location.address: Central Department Store, Ground Floor, East Mall - Grand Indonesia

tip.text: Great industrial interior. Minimalist, earth tone dominated, cozy overall. Coffee is pleasant, plenty of sweet choices (green tea custard pie is good!). Would like to return and try the cinnamon bun!

formattedAddress: Kelapa Gading Square, Italian Walk #B43 (Jl. Raya Boulevard Barat 1)

tip.text: Try the Nasi Kremes Ayam, very very tasty! Escargot seems a favorite, like the amount of garlic they stuffed inside it. If you opt for something spicy, go for the Crab Sambal Pedas. Es Campur is big!

Place is small but nicely decorated. Tofu cheese is good starter, love the dip, very tangy. Chicken pesto rice was tasty. Apple Salsa Dori was quite bland. Try Ginger almond iced tea, very refreshing!
One of the best culinary experiences I ever had! The dinner set is 5 course menu but they have 'suprise' menu served between courses. Ambience is romantic yet energetic. Service is top notch!
Must have Swedish meatballs! Traditional and authentic. Tried the Biff Rydberg as per waiter's reco and it was really really good. Outdoor seating is nice and can ask for blanket if its a bit chilly.
They serve very good herring! Try the sampler of 4 so you can have a bit of every taste. Fresh and authentic. Waiter is helpful and informative as well. Would love to come back!

Their Michelin star is legit! A lot of surprises and twists on the menus  which made the experience very exciting! Waitress is very knowledgeable in explaining the menu. Ambience and interior is nice!
Their fish soup is definitely matched the high rating! Fresh and generous portion. You can ask for extra soup at the counter later on. Very crowded and prepare to be in line but worth the wait!
Very homey and cozy place, not many seatings so better come early. The Pork Chop is mind blowing, juicy, tender and flavorful. Waiters are attentive and helpful, whole dining experience is very nice!
Norwegians have their own meatballs and here they made it so good! Served with mushy peas and lingonberries, exquisite! The fish macaroni pie is also recommended. Place gets packed in the evening.
A cup of cappuccino never fails! It's great to finally have a decent coffee option in the area (which is dominated by SC & CBTL) within walking distance to start the day!

formattedAddress: Indonesia Stock Exchange Building (Tower I Ground Floor)

tip.text: Everything ordered and served on the table were amazing! (Curry, seafood, and many other dishes). Best Thai food I ever had! Mango sticky rice and durian ice cream are particularly delightful!

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330

tip.text: Canelé is the must have! So far the best canelé I had, Paul got one too but very average compare to this one. This particular branch is large but extremely crowded. Prefer the one in Kemang Selatan.
Babaganuc is fresh and perfect to open the meal. Lamb shank is a must, tender and moist, whichever style you choose, it won't disappoint. Pistachio baklava & Rice pudding turned to be superb pair!

venue.name: Kuan Yin Statue & Octagonal Pavilion (观音圣像八宝亭)

tip.text: I'm sure everything behind that glass display won't disappoint. In fact, just close your eyes and point at one if you're an indecisive person like me when it comes to dessert!

location.address: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, Pandawa Lobby
formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, Pandawa Lobby

tip.text: Both exterior and interior design of the hotel are very modern yet warm and homey. Got free upgrade and a chocolate box with a wedding congratulations note from the hotel staff, nice personal touch!
Coffee is meanly delightful. Had cappuccino and loved the composition, perfectly balanced the way it should be. The decorative intriguing statements add the quirkiness of this place, go find some! ;)

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, East Mall (Lower Ground, Shop Unit #EM-LG 37-39)
location.address: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, East Mall

tip.text: French fries with chipotle is the best!! Also love the green chilli chicken, perfect level of spicyness. The rice is cooked perfectly as well. For best refreshing drink, go for green apple iced tea!

tip.text: The Green Tea Ice Cream has very nice texture but the green tea flavor is not as strong as I would expect from a green tea ice cream. Hotdogs are great savoury companions best before the ice cream!

formattedAddress: Ruko Crown Golf Blok A No.32 (Jalan Marina Indah)
location.address: Ruko Crown Golf Blok A No.32

tip.text: Service is top notch. Waitress very attentive and well mannered. The food itself is exquisite! Took my mom for lunch buffet and she liked it very very much. They have best dessert selections here!

Very stylish and cozy small hotel. Scandinavian meets Javanese style in a very elegant way! Staffs are friendly. Food at Waha Kitchen are quite worth it. Really really love the furnitures in the room!

tip.text: Best foie gras I had so far! Salmon pizza is very delicious, truffle oil and onions on the pizza are perfect combination. Sushi rolls come in unique flavors yet each is very very tasty!!

tip.text: Found out they moved to a larger corner just beside their old place. Sweet Morning is as delightful as before. Tried Norwegian Eggs Benedict but it's not as delicious as the European.
Found out the place her
Two best things here are the draft Nest Beer and it's included in happy hour! They also has interesting selections of other beers. They need to work on food though, the yakitori is pretty standard.
Lunch bento set selections are great! Very fresh ingredients! Ask to be seated at sushi bar cause you'll have the chance to see the skillful chefs preparing sashimi, sushi and other dishes.
